{{italic title}} '''''Scarth A.D. 2195''''' is a British erotic science fiction [[comic strip]] created in 1969 <ref>https://www.lambiek.net/artists/r/roca_luis.htm</ref> by writer Jo Addams and illustrator Luis Roca and originally published in British newspaper [[The Sun (United Kingdom)|''The Sun'']]. It was a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] from [[Garth (comic strip)|''Garth'']], which was featured in the ''[[Daily Mirror]]''. After 1972, its title was changed to ''Scarth A.D. 2170''.<ref>http://lambiek.net/artists/r/roca_luis.htm</ref> Les Lilley is also credited with directing the storylines of ''Scarth''.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/obituary-les-lilley-1182586.html Les Lilley], Obituary, ''The Independent''</ref>
